This paper is primarily focused on natural language processing and language modeling, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The use of neural networks and deep learning techniques for language modeling suggests that it could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of affective information in language generation, which could be relevant to research in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper includes experiments and evaluations of the proposed model, which could be classified under cs.SD (Software Engineering).
